column5: Well my buddy and I got out for the evening on opening day on a lake just east of the Sault. Pretty slow action but managed 2 fish one being a personal best. A 10lb 34" walleye gave me the privilege of taking a picture with it. She was a beaut!! Back in the drink she went to make many more babies. All in all it was a good day.
That thing in the fall would be 12-13lbs!!!!
Wow...huge fish!  Nice going.  I'm still waiting to crack the 10 pound mark
wow what an awesome fish!  cheers!
That's a beauty fish, cudos for putting her back! Great job. Scooter
that is like a pike size!.. nice pic and good catchin for sure...
